    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>CHINA SIMPLIFIES STOCK TRADES</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Craig S. Smith</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Smith, Craig S</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>China plans to unify trading systems of its two stock exchanges giving investors ability to trade through single account on both exchanges, which are in Shenzhen and Shanghai (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>China plans to unify the trading systems of its two stock exchanges giving investors the ability to trade through a single account on both exchanges, which are in Shenzhen and Shanghai. The change will be the first step toward broader stock market reforms under consideration, including allowing foreigners to invest directly in shares denominated in China's local currency.</p>
        <p>Craig S. Smith (NYT)</p>
      </block>
